 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. How to Verify Qi2 and WPC Membership?</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Why is WPC (Wireless Power Consortium) membership critical? Without proper membership, factories cannot legally use the Qi logo, exposing your brand to legal risks and product recalls.</p>

 <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Learn more: <a href="/blog/qi2-vs-magsafe-guide" class="text-brandBlue underline">Qi2 vs MagSafe Guide &rarr;</a></p>
 </section>

 <!-- New Section 2: FOD Testing -->
 <section id="fod-testing" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">2. FOD (Foreign Object Detection) Testing</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Core Pain Point:</strong> If users place coins or metal objects on the charger, will it overheat or catch fire? This is the #1 cause of wireless charger returns.</p>
 
 <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-red-700 uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-triangle-exclamation mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
 <path d="M256 0c14.7 0 28.2 8.1 35.2 21l216 400c6.7 12.4 6.4 27.4-.8 39.5S486.1 480 472 480L40 480c-14.1 0-27.2-7.4-34.4-19.5s-7.5-27.1-.8-39.5l216-400c7-12.9 20.5-21 35.2-21zm0 352a32 32 0 1 0 0 64 32 32 0 1 0 0-64zm0-192c-18.2 0-32.7 15.5-31.4 33.7l7.4 104c.9 12.5 11.4 22.3 23.9 22.3 12.6 0 23-9.7 23.9-22.3l7.4-104c1.3-18.2-13.1-33.7-31.4-33.7z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>Expert Recommendation</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Request the factory to demonstrate their FOD algorithm sensitivity. Quality factories should detect metal objects within 2mm of the charging surface.</p>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-green-700 uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-check mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 448 512">
