 <!-- Section 3 -->
 <section id="verify-factory" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">8. How to Verify a Legitimate Factory</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Before committing to any supplier, verify their legitimacy through these steps:</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-6">
 <div class="flex gap-4">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandOrange rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black shrink-0">1</div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Check Business Registration</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify the factory's business license. A legitimate manufacturing facility will have import/export license, ISO 9001 certification capability, and a physical factory address.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="flex gap-4">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandOrange rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black shrink-0">2</div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Request Factory Documentation</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Ask for factory photos (including production lines), employee count verification, business license copy, and ISO certification if claimed.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="flex gap-4">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandOrange rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black shrink-0">3</div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Verify Contact Information</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Legitimate factories have direct phone numbers, company email domains (not Gmail/Yahoo), and respond promptly during business hours.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="flex gap-4">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandOrange rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black shrink-0">4</div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Check Trade Records</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Request export data or check Alibaba trade records. Real factories have documented export history.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
 <h3 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-triangle-exclamation mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
 <path d="M256 0c14.7 0 28.2 8.1 35.2 21l216 400c6.7 12.4 6.4 27.4-.8 39.5S486.1 480 472 480L40 480c-14.1 0-27.2-7.4-34.4-19.5s-7.5-27.1-.8-39.5l216-400c7-12.9 20.5-21 35.2-21zm0 352a32 32 0 1 0 0 64 32 32 0 1 0 0-64zm0-192c-18.2 0-32.7 15.5-31.4 33.7l7.4 104c.9 12.5 11.4 22.3 23.9 22.3 12.6 0 23-9.7 23.9-22.3l7.4-104c1.3-18.2-13.1-33.7-31.4-33.7z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>Red Flag</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">If they only send product catalogs without factory documentation, you're likely dealing with a trading company, not a manufacturer. Check our <a href="/blog/" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">sourcing guides</a> for more tips.</p>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Section 4 -->
 <section id="supplier-questions" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">9. Key Questions to Ask Potential Suppliers</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Use this checklist when evaluating wireless charger factories:</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">About Production</h4>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
 <li>, What is your monthly production capacity?</li>
 <li>, What is your minimum order quantity (MOQ)?</li>
 <li>, How long is the production lead time?</li>
 <li>, Can you provide samples before bulk order?</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">About Quality</h4>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
 <li>, What is your defect rate?</li>
 <li>, What testing do you perform on each unit?</li>
 <li>, Do you have ISO 9001 certification?</li>
 <li>, Can you provide pre-shipment inspection reports?</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">About Certifications</h4>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
 <li>, What certifications do your products have?</li>
 <li>, Are CE, FCC, and Qi certificates available?</li>
 <li>, Who performs the certification testing?</li>
 <li>, Can you assist with additional market certifications?</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">About Customization</h4>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
 <li>, What logo printing options do you offer?</li>
 <li>, Can you customize product colors and packaging?</li>
 <li>, Do you provide custom ID design services?</li>
 <li>, What is the tooling cost for custom molds?</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Section 5 -->
 <section id="qc-process" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">10. Understanding Quality Control Processes</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Quality control is paramount when sourcing wireless chargers. Here's what to expect from a professional factory:</p>
 
 <div class="bg-brandBlue rounded-2xl p-8 text-white mb-8">
 <h4 class="font-black uppercase mb-6">Typical QC Process</h4>
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
 <div class="text-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-white/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3 font-black">1</div>
 <h5 class="font-bold mb-2">IQC</h5>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Incoming Quality Control - Raw material inspection</p>
 </div>
 <div class="text-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-white/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3 font-black">2</div>
 <h5 class="font-bold mb-2">IPQC</h5>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">In-Process Quality Control</p>
 </div>
 <div class="text-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-white/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3 font-black">3</div>
 <h5 class="font-bold mb-2">FQC</h5>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Final Quality Control</p>
 </div>
 <div class="text-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-white/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3 font-black">4</div>
 <h5 class="font-bold mb-2">OQC</h5>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Outgoing Quality Control</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Professional factories typically perform <strong>aging tests</strong> (2-4 hours) on 100% of wireless chargers before shipping. The best factories maintain defect rates below 1%, with some achieving under 0.3%.</p>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-6 mt-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Learn More About Quality Standards</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">For detailed information on international quality management standards, visit <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/62085.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">ISO 9001:2015</a> or learn about <a href="https://www.wirelesspowerconsortium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Qi certification requirements</a> for wireless charging products. Additionally, the <a href="https://www.iec.ch/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">International Electrotechnical Commission</a> provides comprehensive safety standards for electronic products.</p>
 </div>
 </section>

